Timid Tadano is a total wallflower, and that’s just the way he likes it. But all that changes when he finds himself alone in a classroom on the first day of high school with the legendary Komi. He quickly realizes she isn’t aloof—she’s just super awkward. Now he’s made it his mission to help her on her quest to make 100 friends!
(Source: Viz Media)

Music is the light that illuminates people's hearts-- and that "light" was suddenly taken from the world. The world changed the night the black "Kuroya Meteorite" fell. Grotesque monsters known as D2 emerged from the meteorite and began to overrun the land and people. As the D2 were drawn to melodies people played, eventually "music" itself became taboo.
However, those who opposed the monsters appeared. They the "Musicart," girls who draw power from music. They possess the great operas and musical scores of humanity history and use them to defeat the D2.
(Source: Crunchyroll)
Monster ga Afureru Sekai ni Natta kedo, Tayoreru Neko ga Iru kara Daijoubu desu.

On her way home from shopping for dinner, Kujo Ayame, a new member of society who lives with her tortoiseshell cat, Haru, gets caught up in the drastic changes in the world. The changed cityscape, monsters attacking people, and people awakening to their skills....
In the turmoil, Ayame and Haru accidentally succeed in defeating a giant monster, and at that moment, a voice echoes in their heads. ["Kujo Ayame's LV has increased from 1 to 10"]
["Confirming the first named monster defeat in Chaos Frontier Acquired the bonus skill "Search"]
With that as a trigger, Ayame made full use of her search skill to survive in a overflowing with monsters.
Moreover, Ayame is not the only one who has awakened to this skill; her cat Haru has also acquired the useful cheat-level skill "Conversion"!
(Source: GA Novels, translated)

Love is always troubling. You want to have the courage to tell someone how you feel. You want to know who he likes. You want someone to listen to your worries. You want someone to give you a push. I know how you feel, and it hurts. Because I had a past I couldn't forget. And because now I have the "power" to save them.... That's why I, Io Akashi, became an angel. "I've finally found you, the angel of Kuze High." The angel touched the girl's cheek, in order to correct Yuzuki Minato's abnormal tendency to fall in love. This is a slightly mysterious coming-of-age story where memory and love play out softly.
(Source: Dengeki Bunko, translated)
